Bring a large #saucepan{} of water to the boil with @salt{1/2%tsp} for the rigatoni.

Peel and grate the @garlic clove{2}(peeled and grated) (or use a #garlic press{}).

Trim and discard the root and dark green leafy part from the @leek{1}(trimmed and sliced).

When boiling, add the @rigatoni pasta{180%g} to the water and bring back to the boil. Cook until tender, ~{12%minutes}.

Once cooked, drain in a #colander{} and pop back in the pan. Drizzle with @oil{} and stir through to stop it sticking together.

Meanwhile, melt the @butter{20%g} with a drizzle of @oil{} in a large #frying pan{} on medium-high heat.

Once the oil is hot and the butter has melted, add the @British smoked bacon lardons{90%g} and sliced leek and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Cook until the bacon is golden, ~{4-6%minutes}, stirring occasionally. Add the garlic and cook for ~{1%minute}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw meat. Cook bacon thoroughly.

Next, stir in the @vegetable stock paste{10%g} and @water{125%ml}. Bring to the boil, then lower the heat and simmer until slightly reduced, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Meanwhile, zest and cut the @lemon{1}(zested and cut into wedges). Pick the @tarragon{1%bunch} leaves from their stalks and finely chop (discard the stalks).

In a #small bowl{}, combine the lemon zest and half the tarragon. Set your gremolata aside.

Once the sauce has reduced, stir the @creme fraiche{150%g} and @peas{120%g} into the bacon pan. Simmer until the sauce is thickened and piping hot, ~{1-2%minutes}. Add the cooked pasta and toss to combine.

Remove the pan from the heat, then stir through the @grated hard Italian style cheese{40%g} and remaining tarragon.

Taste and season with @salt{}, @pepper{} and a squeeze of lemon from a lemon wedge. Add a splash more water if needed.

Share the pasta primavera between your bowls.

Sprinkle over the tarragon gremolata to finish. Serve with any remaining lemon wedges for squeezing over.

Enjoy!